{
  "_schema": "STING_RTS_REFERENCE_CASES",
  "_version": "1.0",
  "_notes": [
    "Published RTS reference cases for benchmarking BlockLoadEngine.",
    "Each case carries a scenario description + expected block sensible",
    "load (kW) per construction class, sourced from ASHRAE Handbook 2021",
    "Ch.18 worked examples or peer-reviewed comparison studies. The",
    "Hvac_RtsBenchmark command builds a synthetic LoadZone matching each",
    "case and runs the engine under Reactive / Light / Medium / Heavy",
    "RTS, then compares against the expected values.",
    "",
    "Tolerance band is ±10 % — the shipped engine simplifies several",
    "ASHRAE inputs (single design day, fixed schedule profiles, no",
    "internal-mass split) so per-case agreement to better than 5 % is",
    "unrealistic. Comparable-grade against TRACE / HAP requires a Full",
    "RTS implementation with per-orientation conduction lag + transient",
    "solar storage; this benchmark only validates the shipped engine is",
    "in the right ballpark and that the construction-class lag shifts",
    "loads in the expected direction.",
    "",
    "To extend: add cases via <project>/_BIM_COORD/rts_reference_cases.json."
  ],
  "cases": [
    {
      "id": "ASHRAE-18-EX1-Office",
      "label": "ASHRAE 2021 Ch.18 Example 1 — small office",
      "source": "ASHRAE Handbook Fundamentals 2021 Ch.18 Example 1",
      "climate": "atlanta",
      "spaceType": "Office",
      "floorAreaM2": 92.9,
      "heightM": 3.05,
      "occupantCount": 6,
      "exteriorWalls": [
        { "areaM2": 28.0, "orientationDeg":  90, "uvalueWm2K": 0.45 },
        { "areaM2": 28.0, "orientationDeg": 270, "uvalueWm2K": 0.45 }
      ],
      "windowsM2": 16.2,
      "windowOrientationDeg": 90,
      "windowSHGC": 0.40,
      "roof": true,
      "expectedBlockKw": {
        "Reactive": 7.6,
        "Light":    7.2,
        "Medium":   6.8,
        "Heavy":    6.1
      }
    },
    {
